dispensary.name: PotMates Delivery Service - NOW OPEN!
dispensary.description:
PotMates is a premium cannabis delivery only dispensary in Portland, Oregon that offers a convenient and discreet alternative to shopping at retail dispensaries. We sell high-quality cannabis flower, concentrates, and edibles with a focus on relaxation and joy, curated just for you.  

We currently service Portland zip codes only, providing cannabis delivery to neighborhoods such as Multnomah Village, Sellwood, Northwest Portland, North Portland, Northeast Portland, and Southeast Portland.  If you're in Portland, we will deliver to you.  We only deliver to Hillsboro, Beaverton, Clackamas, and Tigard if you are a registered Oregon Medical Marijuana Patient (OMMP).

We have one mission: to make buying and consuming cannabis easier and more fun to do responsibly than ever before. That means working exclusively with local growers like Siren Cannabis, Trichome Farms, and Shadowbox Farms who have strong values, sustainable growing practices, and who give back to their communities. It also means we personally curate our selection to ensure the highest quality product.

products.name: Grown Rogue | Blue Runtz | indoor flower
products.description:
If you need to re-center yourself and you don't have time for a full-on yoga session, then Blue Runtz is the next best thing. It creates a moment of serenity that allows you to walk, untouched, through the eye of the hurricane and emerge ready to handle whatever awaits you on the other side.

Start your aromatherapy by holding the nugs up to your nose and taking a long deep inhale. Allow yourself to be transported to a mostly-sunny day in mid-spring, when the flowers are in full bloom and the berries are just starting to ripen on the vine. It tastes like springtime with sugary notes of vanilla, sprinkled with citrus flavors like blueberry and pear. This delicate floral bouquet is best appreciated with the aid of a bong or a water-filtered vaporizer, otherwise you might miss out on some of the subtler notes.

While you're indulging in the lipsmackingly-good flavors, the Blue Runtz high settles in like river water around an eddy. By the time you lift your head to check out your surroundings, you'll find yourself filled with a serene euphoria, feeling creative but unfocused, without a care in the world, but ready to re-engage with it.
products.strainDescription: Blue Runtz is a indica-dominant hybrid weed strain with an unknown breeder made from a genetic cross between Blueberry and White Runtz, Blue Runtz is 15% THC, making this strain an ideal choice for beginner cannabis consumers. Leafly customers tell us Blue Runtz effects make them feel relaxed, euphoric, and creative. Medical marijuana patients often choose Blue Runtz when dealing with symptoms associated with pain, anxiety, and depression. The dominant terpene of this cannabis strain is limonene. Blue Runtz features an aroma and flavor profile of blueberry, pear, and vanilla. If you’ve smoked, dabbed, or consumed Blue Runtz, tell us about your experience by leaving a strain review.

products.name: Eugreen Farms | Grandi Candi | indoor flower
products.description:
You can tell that Eugreen Farms is just as interested in making their flower taste good as they are in ensuring you get the kind of high you want. This Grandi Candi will leave you feeling fine and dandy, and it has just the most delightful flavor.
Grandi Candy is surprisingly sweet and fruity, like smoking a flavored blunt but without any of the tobacco. You'll get notes of berries so fresh you can almost taste them and a citrusy overtone that makes everything feel new and clean. It's perfect just on its own, whether ground up in a bowl or rolled into a joint, although we recommend using a vaporizer if you're here for the terpenes.
When it comes to the effect, Grandi Candi has that classic weed vibe of letting you just settle into yourself for a minute. As soon as you hit it, you'll feel it in your eyes, then the calm comes in like the tide. Grandi Candi can be overwhelming for people who are new to Mary Jane, but the worst that happens is they get the best nap of their life. It's not the kind you wake up groggy from either—just smoke less next time.
products.strainDescription: Grandi Candi is a strain from Oakland’s Grandiflora Genetics that won’t rot your teeth. It combines some obscure strains, Lemon Cherry Gelato x (E85 x Doggie Bag), for a balanced hybrid smoke that satisfies any sweet tooth. Grandi Candi buds grow compact in a bright purple that can even veer pink, with green accents and stringy orange hairs; heavy trichomes also give them a wet, shiny look. Like a bag of Skittles, the Grandi Candi palate can range from sweet to sour terps, apple to cherry with diesel undernotes. If you’ve smoked, dabbed, or consumed Grandi Candi, tell us about your experience by leaving a strain review.

products.name: Utokia | Mac Daddy | indoor flower
products.description:
Get ready to take it down a notch, because Mac Daddy is here. It's an indica-dominant hybrid, bred from the irresistible MAC#1 and the inimitable Granddaddy Purps. This is a very versatile strain that bends and flexes however you need it, with balanced effects that make it suitable for daytime or nighttime use.

Mac Daddy will transport you to an alternate reality where everything is the same except you—you're calm, centered, and ready for anything. Just the smell of the flower alone is like rejuvenating aromatherapy. Its scent is full of butter and a lingering hint of banana, like a busy restaurant that bakes their own banana bread for brunch every day.

The buds are frosted like an apple cider donut, and you can spot that Granddaddy Purple lineage if you look closely. That's also where Mac Daddy gets its restorative properties. It seeps deep into your joints for a tension-eliminating body high. MAC#1, the other parent, boosts the optimistic side of your imagination, making even the most irritating problems seem understandable, comprehensible, and conquerable. We recommend using a vaporizer and some kind of water filter, as the smoke sometimes hits a little harsh (it's the caryophyllene.)
products.strainDescription: Mac Daddy is an indica-dominant hybrid weed strain made from a genetic cross between unknown parents. This strain is 70% indica and 30% sativa. Mac Daddy is a rare and exclusive strain that is hard to find in most dispensaries. It has dense, grape-shaped nugs with dark green leaves, orange pistils, and frosty trichomes. Mac Daddy is 26% THC, making this strain an ideal choice for experienced cannabis consumers. Leafly customers tell us Mac Daddy effects include feeling euphoric, hungry, and energetic. Medical marijuana patients often choose Mac Daddy when dealing with symptoms associated with pain, anxiety, and depression. Bred by Local Flower, Mac Daddy features flavors like nutty, earthy, and pepper. The dominant terpene of this strain is unknown. The average price of Mac Daddy typically ranges from $30-$50 per eighth. Mac Daddy has a pungent spicy taste and a skunky aroma that will fill the room. If you’ve smoked, dabbed, or consumed Mac Daddy, tell us about your experience by leaving a strain review.

products.name: Eugreen Farms | Lemon Cherry Dosido | indoor flower
products.description:
If your favorite part of the café is the pastry counter, you're going to enjoy this Lemon Cherry Dosido flower. It's rich and toasty, sweet and savory at the same time. You can probably smell it from here. It's hard to say whether the lemon or the cardamom comes through most, but either way, it's a sensory enchantment. Crumble a little bit under your nose for a little sample of what's in store.
The other thing to appreciate about Lemon Cherry Dosido is it has light, springy nugs cling to each other while still leaving little pockets of air. It practically rolls itself into a joint or a blunt wrap. With terpenes like this, you're better off using a vaporizer and a water filter. It just tastes too good to combust!
The effects of Lemon Cherry Dosido are almost immediate. It's like moving to the window seat in the café when there's a break in the clouds—warm and invigorating—the kind of moment you just want to soak in. Unless you know you have low tolerance, in which case this is kind of a heavy strain. One hit may be sufficient, so it helps to have some friends to share the love.

products.name: Grown Rogue | Obama Runtz | indoor flower
products.description:
Did you know that sometimes a rumor can bring a strain into existence? Obama Runtz first appeared as a one-off mention on a video that blew up in 2020, then it made its way into a few Atlanta-based rappers' bars before anyone had the chance to create a strain that could live up to the name. The good news for us is that Grown Rogue has done just that.

Obama Runtz is just the strain to reignite your hope for change. It's bred from a triple cross between Runtz, OG Kush, and Afghani, so its parents are basically Obama Kush and Runtz. The buds are dark and dense with layers of bright forest greens and little oases of deep purple. Obama Runtz has trichomes that are so sparkly you'll want to make sure your flash is off if you try to take pictures of it, otherwise it will be blinding.

It smells down-to-earth with a spicy, floral aroma, and it hits smooth. Obama Runtz has a clear, calming high that will make you feel chatty and confident, perfect for working the room or drumming up support for your latest campaign. It's also great as a party pre-game strain, ideal for smoothing over scene transitions.
products.strainDescription: Obama Runtz is a mysterious marijuana strain popularized by street culture. Obama Runtz is neither related to Runtz nor Obama Kush. Rumors about this strain started with a viral video originating in Atlanta, GA. As of 2020.

products.name: Grown Rogue | Gary Payton | indoor flower
products.description:
Taking a hit is like lining up a clear shot from the free-throw line. Gary Payton is a strain to strum you up and get you into the zone whether you're on the court or on the bench, ready to spring into action. It's named for basketball player Gary "The Glove" Payton who became a nine-time NBA All-Star and Hall of Famer after being an All-American at Oregon State. He wore number 20, and this strain was the twentieth phenotype of a cross between The Y and Snowman.

The best offense is a good defense, and there's nothing directly offensive about this strain. Gary Payton has a rich, spicy flavor that harbors hints of sweetness beneath its herbal diesel exterior. You might get a little bit of mint and nutmeg on the exhale, but it's not a cougher.

The high from Gary Payton is fast, hard-hitting, and long-lasting. It brings on an immediate hit of euphoria and giggles that translate to increased energy. This is a great strain for combatting the Instant Gratification Monkey.
products.strainDescription: A collab between Cookies and Kenny Dumetz of Powerzzzup Genetics, Gary Payton is a highly coveted hybrid marijuana strain bred by Powerzzzup Genetics and named after the NBA Hall of Famer. Combining the Y and Snowman breeds a potent, flavorful, and colorful strain. It has high amounts of THC and almost no CBD, and middle-of-the-road effects that provide an even-keeled experience. Gary Payton has won multiple cannabis cup awards, including 1st place in the 2022 Errl Cup in Arizona in hash form and 2nd in 2022’s The Emerald Cup; strains made from Gary Payton have also garnered wins in Oklahoma and Oregon.

products.name: Utokia | Super Cherry Buff | indoor flower
products.description:
Caveat emptor! Buyer beware! This weed is so captivatingly good you might lose yourself just staring at it before you've even had the chance to put it in your pipe and smoke it. Super Buff Cherry displays every color in the rainbow except for red, which you'll see soon enough once you start to light it up.
If you do manage to get it out of the bag and into the bowl, you're going to have to pass the next gauntlet—the smell. At first whiff, it's light and fruity, but the tickle in your nose will inform you that there are more complex undertones of pepper and pine. It's like starting the day in a vegan café, and you still haven't smoked it yet! What is this Super Buff Cherry stuff, and how did Utokia pull it off?
When you finally get the smoke (or vapor, preferably filtered through a cooling chamber,) into your lungs, you'll discover that all of that sensory overload was only the overture. Super Buff Cherry is the strain of choice for chill, certain to send you soaring to new levels of calm quiet fascination with the world around you. Try looking at that bud again now!
products.strainDescription: Super Cherry is a hybrid weed strain made from a genetic cross between unknown parent strains. This strain is 50% sativa and 50% indica. Super Cherry is 20% THC, making this strain an ideal choice for experienced cannabis consumers. Bred by unknown breeders, the average price of Super Cherry typically ranges from $10-$15 per gram. We are still learning about Super Cherry’s effects, flavors, and medical uses. If you've smoked, dabbed, or consumed Super Cherry, please tell us about your experience by leaving a strain review.

products.name: Grown Rogue | Tropicanna Cherry#8 | indoor flower
products.description:
In today's age of high-potency extracts and vape cartridges with designer terpenes, why would anyone want to smoke boring old low-tech flower? Tropicanna Cherry #8 is the answer. Pick up a nug, squeeze it, and take a deep sniff. You'll see this strain from Grown Rogue can't fully appreciated any other way.
It starts with the nose. Even the casual toker can smell that strong presentation of cherries over a bright twist of tangerine. More sophisticated palates will pick out a sweet floral scent—like chamomile tea with honey, or maybe a touch of grenadine syrup—and that's only the beginning.
Tropicanna Cherry #8 tastes like cherry and fruit. You can expect a burst of citrus on the exhale, certain to ensure that you're going to take more than one hit. The effects kick in as soon as you exhale that second puff. Tropicanna Cherry #8 starts in with a short-lived but very stimulating head high. It's the perfect window of opportunity to decide where you want to ride out the soothing body high. Next thing you know, your eyes will relax, your shoulders will roll back, and you'll be enveloped in a blanket of calming relaxation thicker than a Portland November fog.

products.name: Grown Rogue | Sourdough | indoor flower
products.description:
primary Terpenes:
∂-LIMONENE 0.46%
Β-MYRCENE 0.1%
LINALOOL 0.07%


Picture this: there's a house party in south LA, and everybody's bringing their best weed—Sour Diesel is there, OG Kush, and someone even brought some GSC. Three bowls are flying around the room at the same time, rotating through three different circles, and you can't decide which one you want to jump in on! Well, we have good news for you: some crazy breeders combined all those strains to make Sourdough so you can have your Kush, Cookies, and Diesel, too.
Sourdough has a sweet and doughy gassy odor with an unmistakable presence of cedar and a touch of pine. If the party is in south LA, this stuff smells like it came straight from a mountain lodge in Colorado. Sometimes called Sourdough Kush, this strain is everything we love about weed.
It's got a long-lasting high, enough to keep you going the whole rest of the night. You'll feel an uplifting and gentle euphoria make itself known before the circle even breaks up, and this gives way to a warm tingle that wriggles through the rest of your body. Whether you're headed to the dance floor, the barbecue, or the back room next is entirely up to you.

products.name: Utokia | Apples & Bananas | indoor flower
products.description:
Some strains are best enjoyed by people with a lot of experience and high tolerance. Despite its harmless name, Apples & Bananas is a hard-hitting strain that will knock newbies on their butts, but it has a lot to offer people who know their limits—and it's some absolutely *gorgeous* bud.

Apples & Bananas is a potent hybrid with an incredible pedigree. It’s the result of a cross between Platinum Cookies and Granddaddy Purple that was crossed with Blue Power and _then_ crossed with Gelatti. If you can handle the hit, it will boost you into new plateaus of creativity and insight, stimulating your mind to forge new connections never before conceived.

This soaring head high is accompanied by a stimulating and sometimes arousing body high that’s great for physical activity. It’s good for kinetic art like sculpture or music, for physical exercise like hot yoga, or for enhancing intimacy. While it’s great for getting out, it’s also an experience of its own, so don’t feel bad if you just want to lie down for a while.

Once you're good and up there, staring at these frosted multichromatic nuggets is a trip unto itself. And you can't beat that flavor! It's full of sugary banana, sour apple, and savory diesel notes.
products.strainDescription: Bananas, also known as "Banana," "B1," and "B1 Bananas," is an indica-dominant hybrid marijuana strain. Developed from Leafs by Snoop. this is an indica-dominant hybrid strain often offered in concentrate form, although it can be found in flower form too. This shatter intends to capture sweet tropical flavors of fruit and banana, and offers energizing cerebral effects to fuel creativity.

products.name: Utokia | Banana Acai | indoor flower
products.description:
Picture this: you wake up on a day you when already don't have to go to work. Better yet, it's threatening rain (or possibly already raining,) so you don't have to worry about declining any social invitations. The skyline disappears into a perfect gradient of gray fog, like the system ran out of memory to render the world beyond. There's nothing to keep you from packing a bowl full of Banana Acai and indulging yourself in a day full of "me" time.
Banana Acai is like a smoothie for your mind, tasting of dried berries and banana. It's nourishing down to the very soul of your creativity. With the world outside a blank canvas and no external obligations to throw you out of your groove, you can get into the zone and really make it your own. Grind it up and roll a joint or pack a fat bowl, whatever you have to do to make sure the hits keep on coming because you're about to be on a roll.
Eat a full breakfast with lots of water, and you won't have to worry about any drymouth or redeye interfering with your creative enterprises. The day is all yours!
products.strainDescription: Banana Acai is a hybrid weed strain made from a genetic cross between unknown parent strains. This strain is 50% sativa and 50% indica. Banana Acai is 24% THC, making this strain an ideal choice for experienced cannabis consumers. Bred by unknown breeders, the average price of Banana Acai typically ranges from $10-$15 per gram. We are still learning about Banana Acai’s effects, flavors, and medical uses. If you've smoked, dabbed, or consumed Banana Acai, please tell us about your experience by leaving a strain review.

products.name: Eugreen Farms | Orange Oreoz | indoor flower
products.description:
Orange Oreoz is a unique concoction, something completely new that Eugreen Farms dreamt up because they were dissatisfied with the other Cookiez strains out there. Eugreen Farms prioritizes flavor over everything, and that's the best part about Orange Oreoz—it delivers. Buckle in for a taste that's so realistic you'll forget you just took a hit and not a bite of a delicious creme-filled cookie.
This sativa-leaning hybrid was developed by crossing Tropicana Cookies with a hybrid of GMO and Oreoz. GMO and Oreoz double down on that campfire s'mores flavor associated with Oreoz and that deep sense of peace and calm you get from GMO. Tropicana Cookies brings that brighter citrus flavor to mingle with the cookies, adding an undeniably orange tint to the bouquet.
Do not underestimate this strain! Everything in Orange Oreoz's heritage is a highly potent phenotype from its respective family. Fortunately, there's enough sedative relaxation to keep its sativa-leaning roots from making you fidgety and uncomfortable, while that extra boost of energy from Tropicana Cookies prevents the indica-leaning effects of the other two parents from dragging you into the couch for the rest of the day. For flavor enthusiasts with high tolerance, Oreo Cookiez hits the spot.
products.strainDescription: Oreoz, also known a "Oreo Cookies" and "Oreos," is a potent hybrid marijuana strain made by crossing Cookies and Cream with Secret Weapon. This strain produces a long-lasting and relaxing high. Consumers should take caution as the high potency of Oreoz may be overwhelming to those new to cannabis. This strain has an aroma reminiscent of campfire s'mores, with extra delicious hints of chocolate and diesel. Medical marijuana patients use Oreoz to help relieve symptoms associated with appetite loss, insomnia, chronic stress and depression.

products.name: Coastal Cultivation | Blueberry French Toast | indoor flower
products.description:
Around here, we love a good breakfast strain, and Blueberry French Toast is about as in-your-face delicious as anyone could hope for. One puff, and you'll feel just like you're sitting at the back table of an Amsterdam café, warming your toes by the fire while you watch snow flurries through the window. 

Blueberry French Toast has a smooth, creamy taste and an unmistakably blueberry flavor. If you guessed Blue Dream was part of its heritage, take another hit—you've earned it! It's slightly toastier on the exhale, with a pronounced flavor of earthiness and char that lingers in the air like a proper patisserie. Make sure you corner the bowl if you're smoking from a pipe to preserve that potpourri-like balance of sweet and savory.

This is a wake-and-bake, get-up-and-go strain, which you'll know right from the get-go. Blueberry French Toast announces its presence with a pleasant tingling sensation right in your cheekbones, drawing up a smile of anticipation. It's great for planning your ski runs, mapping the day's hike, or figuring out which item on your to-do list needs to be started first, and it pairs well with friends—the bester, the better.
products.strainDescription: French Toast is an indica-dominant hybrid weed strain made from a genetic cross between Paris OG and Face Off OG. Bred by Archive Seed Bank, French Toast is 16% THC, making this strain an ideal choice for beginner cannabis consumers. Leafly customers tell us French Toast effects make them feel hungry, happy, and relaxed. Medical marijuana patients often choose French Toast when dealing with symptoms associated with stress, anxiety, and depression. The dominant terpene of this cannabis strain is myrcene. French Toast features an aroma and flavor profile of sweet, earthy butter. If you’ve smoked, dabbed, or consumed French Toast, tell us about your experience by leaving a strain review.

products.name: Coastal Cultivation | Carbon Candy | indoor flower
products.description:
Carbon Candy is a spectacular tour-de-force for all of your senses. If you're lucky enough to already be a little bit lifted the first time you see it, it will be easy to get lost in the miniaturized forest of dark green nuggets in the palm of your hand. Look closely, and you'll see rich green textures laced with hues of purple and overlapping light orange hairs. 

It's a cross between Carbon Fiber and Gushers, which you can smell as soon as you pop open the bag. Carbon Candy has an undeniably sweet aroma with a touch of grape tang that will tickle your appetite before you even smoke it. Equally tasty in a joint or a blunt, the flavor turns savory when you light it up, full of herbs and spice.

This is a strain for taking things down a notch. Whether you're coming home from a hectic day of work or your household chores have reached such an unmanageable degree that you're freaking out just trying to figure out where to start, Carbon Candy will buy you a couple hours of pure chill to sort out the signal from the noise. Then it's you who gets to decide what's important.
products.strainDescription: Carbon Candy is a hybrid weed strain made from a genetic cross between Carbon Fiber and Gushers. This strain is 50% sativa and 50% indica. Carbon Candy, also known as Carbon Candy #4, is a creation by Good Day Farm, a brand inspired by a beautiful farm nestled in the hills of Tennessee and the Southern communities that raised them. Carbon Candy is 25% THC, making this strain an ideal choice for experienced cannabis consumers. Leafly customers tell us Carbon Candy effects include feeling happy, relaxed, and euphoric. Medical marijuana patients often choose Carbon Candy when dealing with symptoms associated with stress, pain, and depression. Bred by Good Day Farm, Carbon Candy features flavors like sweet sugar cookies, sour grape, and earthy, herbal undertones. The dominant terpene of this strain is myrcene. The average price of Carbon Candy typically ranges from $10-$15 per gram. Carbon Candy can be enjoyed in various forms, such as flower, blunts, or pre-rolls. If you’ve smoked, dabbed, or consumed Carbon Candy, tell us about your experience by leaving a strain review.

products.name: Coastal Cultivation | Blues OG | indoor flower
products.description:
All right, so first off, this is not your dad's Blue OG. This is a meticulously grown and cared for small batch hybrid produced by Coastal Cultivation that combines the stellar genetics of Orange Cookies, Face Off OG, and Lotus. Let us break that down for you so you know what to expect.
As you can tell from the test results, Blues OG is one hell of a potent strain. 30% THC in a flower is nothing to sneeze at, so make sure you know your limits before you pack a full bowl. It's also packed full of flavor. That's like Coastal Cultivation's whole thing—they're after extraordinary tastes and flavorful experiences—they create phenotypes with robust flavor profiles, and Blues OG does not disappoint. It tastes fresh and clean, bursting with citrus berry flavors over a distinctly skunky musk.
Blues OG is a great bedtime strain. It has an ethereal quality that will start to blur the boundaries before fantasy and reality, perfect for letting your mind wander as you drift off. You'll also notice a heavy, long-lasting body high that will make you want to wrap yourself up in all the blankets and snooze until you start smelling breakfast.
products.strainDescription: Blues, also known as “Livers,” is a famous hybrid strain in the U.K. Its origins are a well-kept secret, but many speculate Blues to be a unique phenotype of Sensi Seeds’ Skunk #1 from the 80’s. Those who have chanced upon this mysterious clone-only strain describe its effects as uplifting, long-lasting, and clear-headed. Blues plants are strong and resilient, growing large buds that give off a sweet berry aroma.

products.name: Eugreen Farms | Carbon Cake | indoor flower
products.description:
What happens when the deep dank cookie funk of Carbon Fiber meets with fruity sugary goodness of Apples & Bananas? Meet Carbon Cake, a strain that walks the edge of lifting you up and calming you down with a tasty sweet and savory flavor that will have you reaching for the bowl more times than you might expect.
Carbon Cake is one of those fantastic hybrids that perfectly blends indica and sativa effects for a satisfying strain you can enjoy any time of the day or night. If you aren't sure what kind of high you want, Carbon Cake will deliver a satisfying experience to tide you over while you make up your mind. At first hit, you'll feel the soaring elation of its Apples & Bananas heritage, filling you with a sense of elated purpose.
Then, as the effects really start to settle in, Carbon Cake will ease you into a state of total serenity, content to contemplate the mysteries of the universe—or just your living room. This is a good strain for taking a walk around your neighborhood, embracing and appreciating the natural beauty that surrounds you. It's also great for hiking, long bus rides, and reading at coffee shops.

products.name: LOWD | Spilt Paint | indoor flower
products.description:
Something we love about all LOWD's flower is that it always lives up to its name. Spilt Paint is loud, filling your space with its aroma as soon as you pop open the pouch. Take a moment to just inhale the scent before you even look at the bud—it's fruity, nutty, and uniquely sweet. The flower isn't bad to look at either. Each nug is bright and fluffy, with a sparkly dusting of trichomes like still-falling snow on a tree branch.
Of course, the journey doesn't stop there. Spilt Paint was born from the combination of two spectacular strains—Georgia Pie and Runtz. Georgia Pie gives the Spilt Paint high a feeling of enchantment, like suddenly anything is possible, and that's great for getting carried away with brand new harebrained schemes. One reason it's called "Spilt Paint" is you won't mind getting a little messy with whatever work of creativity currently occupying your space as you waltz with your muse.
Then there's Runtz, which gives you the stamina to keep dancing long into the night. It brings the motivation to meet Georgia Pie's inspiration and gives Spilt Paint that extra "oomph" to move you from just thinking about something to actually doing it.

products.name: LOWD | Toe Jam | indoor flower
products.description:
Toe Jam is a hot new phenotype from LOWD that does not sound nearly as appealing as it hits. While some varieties are bred from Cheese and DJ Short Flo—a decidedly stinkier strain with the same name—this one is bred from Gelato 41 and Undertow. Gelato 41 leans slightly sativa while Undertow leans indica, and when they get together, the combination is tasty, aromatic, and sure to pull you under.
Unlike Cheese strains, you can put this bud right up to your nose and inhale deeply. A bright bouquet of oranges and mint rise to the surface, underscored by rich notes of earth, pine, and a little bit of diesel. The frosted pale green buds have some subtle purple accents if you break them apart to look inside, and we recommend using a kief-catching grinder to make sure you don't lose any of those crystalized trichomes in the process.
Toe Jam hits your brain like a late-stage Childish Gambino album—it might seem disorienting at first, but you quickly relax into the soothing power of its tasty grooves. This is a sociable high worth sharing with a couple close friends, or a rejuvenating introspective journey if you're smoking on your own tonight.

products.name: Dr. Jolly’s | Sour Diesel Premium Extract | 1g
products.description:
There are two reasons they call it diesel. The obvious one is that it has a pungent aroma like diesel fuel that catches you in the back of the nostrils—even in a concentrate. You can thank β-caryophyllene for clearing out your sinuses. The second reason is that this strain will make you rev up your engine. You'll want to throw open your blinds, your windows, maybe even your door and dance right out into the street.

Maybe you've been feeling down lately, a little lazy, or just plain bored, but if you're looking for a way to face your problems head-on, Sour Diesel is just the fuel to help you get there. Though technically only a sativa-dominant hybrid, this strain feels like a landrace sativa with its speedy cerebral head high. This particular phenotype is a little more on the chill side with a solid showing from β-myrcene, but it's still predominantly a pick-me-up strain.

Dr. Jolly's uses a subcritical extraction process to preserve as much of the plant's original entourage effect as possible. Those terpenes are from the original fresh frozen flower, so you can experience all the sweet and sour diesely flavor of the original bud.
products.strainDescription: Sour Diesel, also known as "Sour D" and "Sour Deez," is a popular hybrid marijuana strain made by crossing Chemdawg and Super Skunk. Sour Diesel effects are dreamy, cerebral, fast-acting and energizing. This strain features a pungent flavor profile that smells like diesel. Medical marijuana patients choose Sour Diesel to help relieve symptoms associated with depression, pain, and stress. Fun fact: Sour Diesel first became popular in the early 1990s and has been legendary ever since.

products.name: Dr. Jolly’s | Sour Cherries Nug Run | 1g
products.description:
Also known as "Sour Cherry," Sour Cherries is another delectable varietal from Dr. Jolly's. While the flower might make you pucker, this Nug Run is extracted exclusively from dried and cured buds, so some of the sour has worn off. Not the terpenes, though, and you can tell from its THC content that this strain hits hard.

It's great if you can roll with it. Sour Cherries starts with a strong, calming body buzz that settles in like a weighted blanket draped across your chest. As you start to sink physically, the head high creeps up on you with what can best be described as pleasant amnesia. Whatever might have been bothering you before you took a hit will quickly dissolve as your mood floats away, detached from the burdens of reality.

Diamonds are such a concentrated form of cannabis extract that you can expect to get blasted right into space. The only downside is that it's a little light on flavor—you can expect just a little apple and some woodiness—but some people like a strain that's not very pungent.

For those of you with high tolerance, Alien ET is a wonderful, transportive experience that pushes all the right buttons for extraterrestrial exploration. It has a buzzy physical high that can be both invigorating and somewhat stimulating, which is good for explorations of an altogether different nature. Whether you're flying solo or with a partner (or a whole crew, we don't judge,) you'll be spine-tinglingly attuned to every sensation.

Alien ET also offers a happy and creative head high, elevating your game so you can finally get something accomplished that you can feel good about. Whether it's doing house work, yard work, or artwork, this peppy strain will keep you motivated to the finish line.

products.strainDescription: Garlic Bud is a classic indica strain from the 90's, bred by The Seed Bank (now known as Sensi Seeds) using Afghani genetics. Its name is only loosely tied to Garlic Bud's aroma, which smells a lot more like tangy musk and spice than anything you'd throw in your stir fry. This pungent-smelling indica expresses a duality of effects: heavy body effects that crush insomnia and pain coupled with an invigorating cerebral buzz. A 7 or 8 week flowering time is all Garlic Bud needs to reach full maturation, finishing with sizeable yields.

products.name: Dr. Jolly’s | Platinum Point Break Premium Extract | 1g
products.description:
Has anyone ever told you that you don't know how to switch off, that you work too hard, or that you never seem to be able to take a break? If so, this strain is for you. Point Break is an excellent choice for winding down with a double feature in your living room or partaking in your favorite rejuvenation exercise.

It smells sweet and sour at the same time, like the sunny beaches of Santa Monica. Point Break has notes of tangerine over a bed of woody pine and fresh earth. It delivers an effect that is lifted and euphoric at the same time, dispelling any cloudy thoughts from your mind.

After it's had the chance to lift you up, Point Break settles you back down with a heavy body high full of stoney relaxation. If you've never seen "Point Break”, this would be a great time to pop in the DVD. Just make sure to follow it up with “Bad Boyz II”, or you'll be missing out on some right proper action. Oh, and it also pairs well with surfing, so long as you're indulging after you hit the waves—you're going to need your reaction time intact if you want to actually catch any.
products.strainDescription: Point Break is a strain worthy of a Keanu Reeves cameo—High Times deemed it a Strain of the Day for 4/20 week 2023. This hybrid from Surfr Seeds thrills with magenta, trichome-slick buds and fills the nose with the paradisal terps of its Tropicana Cookies (Mtn Cut) x Trophy Wife parents. If you’ve smoked, dabbed, or consumed Point Break, tell us about your experience by leaving a strain review.

Gelato Cake is a potent indica-dominant marijuana strain made by crossing the creamy berry of Gelato #33 and the vanilla frosting of Wedding Cake. Part of the Cookie strain family, Gelato Cake is very popular across North America and beyond. Consumers should know that Gelato Cake is potent and is best for experienced users. Gelato Cake is known to cause full-body sedation which can last up to a few hours, so it's best to enjoy this strain before bed or during a relaxing night at home watching movies. Medical patients choose Gelato Cake for stimulating appetite and relieving stiffness, pain and stress. Growers choose to grow Gelato Cake for its creamy, berry, gassy and vanilla frosting aromas. Gelato Cake can be grown indoors and outdoors, with a flowering time of 8-9 weeks.

Gelato Cake Strain Highlights


	Type: indica-dominant
	Tastes like: berries and vanilla
	Feels like: sedating

products.name: Dr. Jolly’s | Orange Chemdawg Nug Run | 1g
products.description:
What could make Chemdawg even better? How about the zesty tang of oranges? That's the nice thing about these nug run concentrates from Dr. Jolly's—they take the time to really cure the buds so the flavors have the chance to marinate. Orange Chemdawg is an indica-leaning hybrid with powerful effects and an equally potent flavor.

Orange Chemdawg has a spicy taste with strong notes of diesel fuel and a fruity citrus undertone that gives it that extra special something you'll really taste on the exhale. Be forewarned—the smell is so pungent that everyone around will know exactly what you're up to. This is not a stealth strain!

As loud as it is, Orange Chemdawg is great for when you're feeling down, offering a cerebral high that sparks creativity and positive well-being. It comes complete with a stony body high, so if you take two hits it will assuage any lingering anxieties that might be keeping you up at night. Orange Chemdawg is also great for intimate conversations with friends you wish you knew better. It might hit hard, but that can help you get on the same level as each other to really dig in. Enjoy the daze!
products.strainDescription: Chemdawg, officially named "Chemdog," is a hybrid marijuana strain grown and spread by the breeder Chemdog since 1991. In a Leafly interview, Chemdog relates how Chemdog came from what was thought to be Northern California bag seed, via a Colorado Grateful Dead concert. Chem 91, Chem 4, and Chem Sis are all variations on Chemdog. The original name Chemdog came from two names for the same bud "Chem" and "Dog bud." Chemdog evolved into the variation 'Chemdawg' over time and distance as other growers and breeders propagated it, with the latter name becoming more dominant. Leafly customers tell us Chemdawg effects include feeling euphoric, uplifted, and creative. Medical marijuana patients often choose Chemdawg when dealing with symptoms associated with stress, anxiety, and pain. Chemdog is a staple strain in cannabis and may be a source of powerhouse strains like Sour Diesel and OG Kush, Chemdog is known for its distinct, diesel-like aroma. Pungent and sharp, you’ll be able to smell this strain from a mile away. Cannabis newbies be warned: Chemdog tends to be very potent. Consumers can expect to have a cerebral experience, coupled with a strong heavy-bodied feeling.

products.name: Dr. Jolly’s | Wedding Cake Live Resin | 1g
products.description:
Wedding Cake is a great strain for taking things down a notch, 
and this Live Resin from Dr. Jolly's preserves all the original terpenes that other extraction processes usually lose.

Its lineage is complicated—some growers breed it from Cherry Pie and GSC while others use Triangle Kush crossed with Animal Mints—and you know Dr. Jolly's is keeping their personal private recipe close to the vest. Still, everything we love about it is here. Just like a real wedding, it doesn't matter much where it comes from, so long as everyone's happy.

Wedding Cake has a rich flavor, full of wood and hops that finishes with a hint of flowers and tang. It's perfect for keeping your cool whether you're out at a bachelorette party or staying inside. 

Once the high sets in, you'll find yourself relaxed, sleepy, and a little hungry. This is a good afterparty strain, for winding down when you're not quite ready to pack it all the way in for the night. Its sativa parents contribute a little bit of creativity and euphoria, so you'll still have energy enough to make new friends while reconnecting with the old. (Remember, one is silver, and the other's gold!)
products.strainDescription: Wedding Cake, also known as "Triangle Mints #23," is a potent type of indica-hybrid marijuana strain made by crossing Triangle Kush with Animal Mints. Fun fact: In Canada, this strain is known as Pink Cookies. The Wedding Cake strain provides relaxing and euphoric effects that calm the body and mind. This strain yields a rich and tangy flavor profile with undertones of earthy pepper. Medical marijuana patients choose Wedding Cake to help relieve symptoms associated with pain, insomnia and appetite loss. Consumers with a low THC tolerance should enjoy this strain with an extra slice of care due to its high THC content. Wedding Cake has soared in popularity over the years and was named Leafly Strain of the Year in 2019.

products.name: Dr. Jolly’s | White Truffle Sauce on the Rocks | 1g
products.description:
The reason truffles are considered a delicacy isn't because of the way they taste on their own or how they allegedly bring out the underlying flavors of a dish by providing a boring one-dimensional flavor as a backdrop—it's because they're impossible to cultivate, requiring specially-trained pigs to sniff them out beneath the tree roots under which they grow. And there is none more valuable, more delectable, more sought-after than the white truffle, which gives this stain its name.

White Truffle is named for two things: its flavor, and the frosting of trichomes that makes its round nugs look like big puffy truffles. Sauce on the Rocks is one of Dr. Jolly's terpier extracts, and the earthy scent of skunk and garlic certainly is reminiscent of the real deal—but that's not why we like it.

The best thing about White Truffle is how it makes you feel. It starts with a euphoric, cerebral head rush that will inject some spontaneity into your day, giving you new exciting ideas for what to do next. While your mind is distracted, your body will start to sink into a peaceful and relaxing stone that will keep you on that track.
products.strainDescription: White Truffle is an indica-dominant hybrid marijuana strain that is a type of Gorilla Butter. This strain produces a quick-hitting head high that will clear your mind of worry. Eventually, these effects can be felt throughout your body, leaving you in a relaxing trance. Consumers who have enjoyed White Truffle weed describe the high as "calming and slightly buzzy." This strain is best when enjoyed after a long day of work or during the evening hours to relax and unwind. White Truffle features a savory and earthy flavor profile accompanied by a mild skunky aroma. Medical marijuana patients choose White Truffle to relieve symptoms associated with stress and fatigue. White Truffle is dusted by frosty white trichomes and features dark brown hairs. It comes from the small breeder Fresh Coast Genetics in Michigan, although Parabellum Genetics has a strain of the same name. If you've smoked, dabbed, or consumed White Truffle cannabis before, tell us about your experience by leaving a review.

products.name: Echo Electuary | Original Glue Live Budder | 1g
products.description:
Sometimes, the present moment is just so good you want to get stuck there, and that's where Original Glue comes in. It's a legendary hybrid that earned its reputation back in the prohibition era when every cultivar had to defend its place under the grow light. The term "perfectly balanced" gets thrown around a lot with hybrids, but in this case, it's true—Original Glue is as close as you can get to the perfect hybrid.

Aside from its potency, this is a great strain for a first-time dabber. The high starts with a pleasant lifting sensation that opens your mind to the positive possibilities that surround you, then gives way to the best kind of body high that loosens you up and sticks you to whatever surface you might be sitting on. It’s got a light, woody flavor with hints of pine and juniper, so it shouldn’t lead to much coughing at all.

Original Glue is named for the way it glues you to the couch, so we recommend it for activities where you wouldn’t be likely to get up anyway, such as watching a movie, playing video games, or going for a long soak in a hot tub.
products.strainDescription: Gorilla Glue is a hybrid weed strain made from a genetic cross between Chem’s Sister, Sour Dubb, and Chocolate Diesel. This strain is 37% sativa and 63% indica. “Gorilla Glue”, also known as “Original Glue” or “GG4”, is a potent strain that delivers heavy-handed euphoria and relaxation, leaving you feeling “glued” to the couch. Its chunky, resin-covered buds fill the room with pungent earthy and sour aromas inherited from its parent strains. Gorilla Glue is 20% THC, making this strain an ideal choice for experienced cannabis consumers. Leafly customers tell us Gorilla Glue effects include feeling relaxed, sleepy, and hungry. Medical marijuana patients often choose Gorilla Glue when dealing with symptoms associated with stress, anxiety, and pain. Bred by GG Strains LLC, Gorilla Glue features flavors like pungent, pine, and earthy. The dominant terpene of this strain is caryophyllene. The average price of Gorilla Glue typically ranges from $10-$15 per gram. Gorilla Glue is a multiple award-winning strain that has taken first place in both the Michigan and Los Angeles 2014 Cannabis Cups, as well as the High Times Jamaican World Cup in 2015. It is a fast-growing strain that produces large yields of sticky buds with a flowering time of 9-10 weeks. If you’ve smoked, dabbed, or consumed Gorilla Glue, tell us about your experience by leaving a strain review.

products.name: Eugreen Farms | Georgia GMO Live Rosin | 1g
products.description:
Every once in a while—slightly more frequently than a Blue Moon, but just as phenomenal—we'll get a Flow (creative)  strain that presses all the right buttons. This Georgia GMO rosin from Eugreen Farms is just such a strain. If you're at all creatively inclined, you'll want to pick this up immediately to make sure you don't miss out on the opportunity.
Georgia GMO, as you can guess from the name, is a cross between the inimitable Georgia Pie and the notorious GMO. GMO gives it a balanced sense of peaceful relaxation that's as easy on your mind as it is on your body, while Georgia Pie stimulates your imagination and inspires the sort of creative breakthroughs that can really reinvigorate your practice.
When it comes to the flavor, Georgia GMO hits all the notes of a down-south highway diner—it's pungent with an aroma of spice and coffee, but it has a smooth doughy taste with a hint of cherry rhubarb pie. At 77% THC, it's not as potent as some of our other concentrates, but we actually like it that way. When a concentrate is too strong, it can actually interfere with the creative process.

products.name: Echo Electuary | Apples & Bananas Live Budder | 1g
products.description:
Some strains are best enjoyed by people with a lot of experience and high tolerance. Despite its harmless name, Apples & Bananas is a hard-hitting strain that will knock newbies on their asses, but it has a lot to offer people who know their limits. 

Apples & Bananas is a potent hybrid with an incredible pedigree. It’s the result of a cross between Platinum Cookies and Granddaddy Purple that was crossed with Blue Power and then crossed with Gelatti. If you can handle the hit, it will boost you into new plateaus of creativity and insight, stimulating your mind to forge new connections never before conceived.

This soaring head high is accompanied by a stimulating and sometimes arousing body high that’s great for physical activity. It’s good for kinetic art like sculpture or music, for physical exercise like hot yoga, or for enhancing intimacy. While it’s great for getting out, it’s also an experience of its own, so don’t feel bad if you just want to lie down for a while.

Apples & Bananas is also one of the tastier concentrates on the market. It’s got a flavor that’s sweet and fruity, full of sugary banana, sour apple, and savory diesel notes.
products.strainDescription: Bananas, also known as "Banana," "B1," and "B1 Bananas," is an indica-dominant hybrid marijuana strain. Developed from Leafs by Snoop. this is an indica-dominant hybrid strain often offered in concentrate form, although it can be found in flower form too. This shatter intends to capture sweet tropical flavors of fruit and banana, and offers energizing cerebral effects to fuel creativity.

products.name: Echo Electuary | RS-11 Live Budder | 1g
products.description:
As fun as it is to get completely blitzed, sometimes you want a high that still leaves you able to function, something that's calming and relaxing, but won't knock you out. RS-11 is great for days when you have things to do, but you want to be cool about it—the very definition of a wake-and-bake strain.

This Live Budder from Echo Electuary is a spreadable paste that's super easy to work with. Dab a little RS-11 into your banger, and your nose will start to smile with the extra fruity flavor floating up into your nostrils. It smells like the gelato cooler at your favorite ice cream parlor, full of cherry, berry, and just a hint of frosty pine. 

RS-11 starts with a stimulating high that promotes alertness and congeniality, which is ideal for knocking out your to-do list. That burst of positive productivity is followed by a deeply penetrating body high that is almost perfectly timed for you to take a well-deserved break after all that work, or maybe even kick off for the rest of the day. Mind the drop though—once your butt hits the couch, RS-11 will keep it there until the high wears off.
products.strainDescription: RS11, also known as "RS-11" and "Rainbow Sherbert #11," is a hybrid weed strain that Deo Farms made by crossing the OZ Kush project Pink Guava with a Sunset Sherbert. RS-11 was bred by Deo Farms of Oakland, CA, the maker of Zoap. RS-11 was selected by Wizard Trees of LA, along with RS-54. In 2023, many cultivators grow RS-11 across the US. RS-11 is more relaxing than energizing. Consumers who have smoked this strain report feeling calm, and sedated, but still mentally alert. The flavor profile is extra fruity with hints of sour citrus. RS11 flower provides a smooth smoke and a lingering sweet and spicy aroma. Medical marijuana patients say they smoke this strain when experiencing mild pain.

products.name: Select | Cliq Battery
products.description:
Select has really done something neat with Cliq. It is the result of years of research and development with one goal in mind: creating an innovative high-quality vaporizer that is durable, convenient, and comfortable. Using a rechargeable battery and interchangeable Pods, Cliq delivers a vape with unparalleled refinement.

This battery has three voltage settings, (2.8, 3.2, and 3.6,) which allow you to dial in the perfect temperature. Low voltage lets you taste all the delicious terpenes contained within Select’s Elite oils while higher voltages produce voluminous clouds of vapor. We recommend keeping it on low or medium to get the full range of flavor. The battery is encased in an extruded stainless steel shell for durability and coated in a matte-finish automotive grade paint for a distinctive feel.

It charges with USB-C so you don’t have to keep up with extra cables. For convenience and security, Cliq Pods connect to the battery with high powered magnets that give it that signature “click” when it all comes together. The best part is that it’s breath-activated so there’s no risk of it coming on in your pocket or bag and wasting oil.

This battery is free with the purchase of at least one Select Cliq Pod. One battery per order, and or customer while supplies last.

How to use the Select Cliq Battery

Your Cliq battery comes with a USB to USB-C charging cable that plugs into a port at the bottom. While your battery might already have some juice when you get it, we recommend charging it until the indicator light turns green for best results.

Once charged, all you have to do is insert your Cliq Pod into the appropriate slot on top of the battery. Magnets will bring the two parts together with a satisfying click and the light on the front will light up with the color of your current voltage setting—blue, yellow, or green.

There’s a single button that’s used to change the voltage setting or preheat the coil.

Click the button three times to change voltage settings, and it will cycle between 2.8v (blue), 3.2v (yellow), and 3.6v (green).
Click the button two times and it will preheat the coil to help dislodge any air bubbles that may still be attached to the cotton. This is usually only necessary during cold weather or during extended exposure to the outdoors.
To hit a Cliq vaporizer, just put it to your mouth and inhale. You should see the indicator light up blue, yellow, or green (depending on your setting) for up to five seconds of continuous draw. After five seconds, the light will blink several times and then fall dim. The Cliq Battery has this safety feature to prevent overheating, which is part of what makes this design so safe.
